{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":645,"text":"A herd of wildebeests, a shoal of fish,"},{"time":3196,"text":"a flock of birds."},{"time":4825,"text":"Many animals gather in large groups"},{"time":6893,"text":"that are among the most wonderful spectacles"},{"time":8879,"text":"in the natural world."},{"time":10597,"text":"But why do these groups form?"},{"time":13321,"text":"The common answers include things like"},{"time":14958,"text":"seeking safety in numbers or hunting in packs"},{"time":17924,"text":"or gathering to mate or breed,"},{"time":20420,"text":"and all of these explanations,"},{"time":22088,"text":"while often true,"},{"time":23325,"text":"make a huge assumption about animal behavior,"},{"time":26368,"text":"that the animals are in control of their own actions,"},{"time":29545,"text":"that they are in charge of their bodies."},{"time":31796,"text":"And that is often not the case."}]},{"cues":[{"time":35223,"text":"This is Artemia, a brine shrimp."},{"time":38147,"text":"You probably know it better as a sea monkey."},{"time":40911,"text":"It's small, and it typically lives alone,"},{"time":42906,"text":"but it can gather in these large red swarms"},{"time":45983,"text":"that span for meters,"},{"time":48230,"text":"and these form because of a parasite."},{"time":51320,"text":"These shrimp are infected with a tapeworm."},{"time":54006,"text":"A tapeworm is effectively a long, living gut"},{"time":56257,"text":"with genitals at one end and\na hooked mouth at the other."},{"time":59145,"text":"As a freelance journalist, I sympathize."},{"time":61680,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":63835,"text":"The tapeworm drains nutrients from Artemia's body,"},{"time":66743,"text":"but it also does other things."},{"time":68820,"text":"It castrates them,"},{"time":70440,"text":"it changes their color from transparent to bright red,"},{"time":75158,"text":"it makes them live longer,"},{"time":76674,"text":"and as biologist Nicolas Rode has found,"},{"time":79031,"text":"it makes them swim in groups."},{"time":82390,"text":"Why? Because the tapeworm,\nlike many other parasites,"},{"time":85842,"text":"has a complicated life cycle"},{"time":87423,"text":"involving many different hosts."},{"time":89687,"text":"The shrimp are just one step on its journey."},{"time":92091,"text":"Its ultimate destination is this,"},{"time":94703,"text":"the greater flamingo."},{"time":96650,"text":"Only in a flamingo can the tapeworm reproduce,"},{"time":99675,"text":"so to get there, it manipulates its shrimp hosts"},{"time":102964,"text":"into forming these conspicuous colored swarms"},{"time":106055,"text":"that are easier for a flamingo to spot"},{"time":108772,"text":"and to devour,"},{"time":110331,"text":"and that is the secret of the Artemia swarm."},{"time":113263,"text":"They aren't sociable through their own volition,"},{"time":115426,"text":"but because they are being controlled."},{"time":117502,"text":"It's not safety in numbers."},{"time":119196,"text":"It's actually the exact opposite."},{"time":121055,"text":"The tapeworm hijacks their brains and their bodies,"},{"time":124096,"text":"turning them into vehicles"},{"time":125492,"text":"for getting itself into a flamingo."}]},{"cues":[{"time":129459,"text":"And here is another example"},{"time":130889,"text":"of a parasitic manipulation."},{"time":133415,"text":"This is a suicidal cricket."},{"time":136391,"text":"This cricket swallowed the \nlarvae of a Gordian worm,"},{"time":139695,"text":"or horsehair worm."},{"time":141588,"text":"The worm grew to adult size within it,"},{"time":143744,"text":"but it needs to get into water in order to mate,"},{"time":146782,"text":"and it does that by releasing proteins"},{"time":149000,"text":"that addle the cricket's brain,"},{"time":151188,"text":"causing it to behave erratically."},{"time":153352,"text":"When the cricket nears a body of water,"},{"time":155307,"text":"such as this swimming pool,"},{"time":156926,"text":"it jumps in and drowns,"},{"time":159183,"text":"and the worm wriggles out"},{"time":160908,"text":"of its suicidal corpse."},{"time":164764,"text":"Crickets are really roomy. Who knew?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":168367,"text":"The tapeworm and the Gordian worm are not alone."},{"time":171582,"text":"They are part of an entire cavalcade"},{"time":173302,"text":"of mind-controlling parasites,"},{"time":175379,"text":"of fungi, viruses, and worms and insects and more"},{"time":179328,"text":"that all specialize in subverting and overriding"},{"time":181901,"text":"the wills of their hosts."},{"time":184110,"text":"Now, I first learned about this way of life"},{"time":185847,"text":"through David Attenborough's \"Trials of Life\""},{"time":188340,"text":"about 20 years ago,"},{"time":190062,"text":"and then later through a wonderful book called"},{"time":191764,"text":"\"Parasite Rex\" by my friend Carl Zimmer."},{"time":194438,"text":"And I've been writing about\nthese creatures ever since."},{"time":196581,"text":"Few topics in biology enthrall me more."},{"time":199392,"text":"It's like the parasites have subverted my own brain."},{"time":203098,"text":"Because after all, they are always compelling"},{"time":205709,"text":"and they are delightfully macabre."},{"time":206997,"text":"When you write about parasites,"},{"time":208389,"text":"your lexicon swells with phrases like"},{"time":210473,"text":"\"devoured alive\" and \"bursts out of its body.\""},{"time":213519,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":214756,"text":"But there's more to it than that."},{"time":216296,"text":"I'm a writer, and fellow writers in the audience"},{"time":218398,"text":"will know that we love stories."},{"time":221107,"text":"Parasites invite us to resist the allure"},{"time":223500,"text":"of obvious stories."},{"time":225350,"text":"Their world is one of plot twists"},{"time":227660,"text":"and unexpected explanations."},{"time":231267,"text":"Why, for example,"},{"time":232763,"text":"does this caterpillar"},{"time":234941,"text":"start violently thrashing about"},{"time":236915,"text":"when another insect gets close to it"},{"time":238583,"text":"and those white cocoons that it seems"},{"time":240840,"text":"to be standing guard over?"},{"time":242278,"text":"Is it maybe protecting its siblings?"},{"time":245374,"text":"No."},{"time":246823,"text":"This caterpillar was attacked"},{"time":248280,"text":"by a parasitic wasp which laid eggs inside it."},{"time":251499,"text":"The eggs hatched and the young wasps"},{"time":252933,"text":"devoured the caterpillar alive"},{"time":254247,"text":"before bursting out of its body."},{"time":255918,"text":"See what I mean?"},{"time":258193,"text":"Now, the caterpillar didn't die."},{"time":261031,"text":"Some of the wasps seemed to stay behind"},{"time":263616,"text":"and controlled it into defending their siblings"},{"time":266953,"text":"which are metamorphosing"},{"time":268587,"text":"into adults within those cocoons."},{"time":270607,"text":"This caterpillar is a head-banging \nzombie bodyguard"},{"time":274146,"text":"defending the offspring"},{"time":275447,"text":"of the creature that killed it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":277669,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":281535,"text":"We have a lot to get through. \nI only have 13 minutes. (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":285830,"text":"Now, some of you are probably just"},{"time":287641,"text":"desperately clawing for some solace"},{"time":289859,"text":"in the idea that these things are oddities"},{"time":292119,"text":"of the natural world, that they are outliers,"},{"time":294050,"text":"and that point of view is understandable,"},{"time":295870,"text":"because by their nature, parasites are quite small"},{"time":298248,"text":"and they spend a lot of their time"},{"time":299588,"text":"inside the bodies of other things."},{"time":302542,"text":"They're easy to overlook,"},{"time":304313,"text":"but that doesn't mean that they aren't important."},{"time":306898,"text":"A few years back, a man called Kevin Lafferty"},{"time":309103,"text":"took a group of scientists\ninto three Californian estuaries"},{"time":312472,"text":"and they pretty much weighed and dissected"},{"time":314220,"text":"and recorded everything they could find,"},{"time":316215,"text":"and what they found"},{"time":317443,"text":"were parasites in extreme abundance."},{"time":320659,"text":"Especially common were trematodes,"},{"time":322703,"text":"tiny worms that specialize in castrating their hosts"},{"time":325353,"text":"like this unfortunate snail."},{"time":327899,"text":"Now, a single trematode is tiny, microscopic,"},{"time":330788,"text":"but collectively they weighed as much"},{"time":332587,"text":"as all the fish in the estuaries"},{"time":334773,"text":"and three to nine times more than all the birds."},{"time":338480,"text":"And remember the Gordian worm that I showed you,"},{"time":340474,"text":"the cricket thing?"},{"time":341862,"text":"One Japanese scientist called Takuya Sato"},{"time":344415,"text":"found that in one stream,"},{"time":346111,"text":"these things drive so many crickets"},{"time":348082,"text":"and grasshoppers into the water"},{"time":349381,"text":"that the drowned insects"},{"time":350690,"text":"make up some 60 percent of the diet of local trout."},{"time":354994,"text":"Manipulation is not an oddity."},{"time":357928,"text":"It is a critical and common part"},{"time":360048,"text":"of the world around us,"},{"time":361939,"text":"and scientists have now found"},{"time":363460,"text":"hundreds of examples of such manipulators,"},{"time":365942,"text":"and more excitingly, they're starting to understand"},{"time":368379,"text":"exactly how these creatures control their hosts."}]},{"cues":[{"time":372437,"text":"And this is one of my favorite examples."},{"time":374961,"text":"This is Ampulex compressa,"},{"time":377418,"text":"the emerald cockroach wasp,"},{"time":379642,"text":"and it is a truth universally acknowledged"},{"time":381936,"text":"that an emerald cockroach wasp in possession"},{"time":383579,"text":"of some fertilized eggs"},{"time":385375,"text":"must be in want of a cockroach."},{"time":387841,"text":"When she finds one,"},{"time":389041,"text":"she stabs it with a stinger"},{"time":391252,"text":"that is also a sense organ."},{"time":392701,"text":"This discovery came out three weeks ago."},{"time":395372,"text":"She stabs it with a stinger that is a sense organ"},{"time":397677,"text":"equipped with small sensory bumps"},{"time":399471,"text":"that allow her to feel the distinctive texture"},{"time":402026,"text":"of a roach's brain."},{"time":404133,"text":"So like a person blindly rooting about in a bag,"},{"time":407174,"text":"she finds the brain, and she injects it with venom"},{"time":409651,"text":"into two very specific clusters of neurons."},{"time":413852,"text":"Israeli scientists Frederic Libersat and Ram Gal"},{"time":416935,"text":"found that the venom is a\nvery specific chemical weapon."},{"time":420660,"text":"It doesn't kill the roach, nor does it sedate it."},{"time":423204,"text":"The roach could walk away"},{"time":425331,"text":"or fly or run if it chose to,"},{"time":428356,"text":"but it doesn't choose to,"},{"time":430231,"text":"because the venom nixes its motivation to walk,"},{"time":433611,"text":"and only that."},{"time":434725,"text":"The wasp basically un-checks\nthe escape-from-danger box"},{"time":438431,"text":"in the roach's operating system,"},{"time":440271,"text":"allowing her to lead her helpless victim"},{"time":443504,"text":"back to her lair by its antennae"},{"time":445615,"text":"like a person walking a dog."},{"time":448254,"text":"And once there, she lays an egg on it,"},{"time":449931,"text":"egg hatches, devoured alive, bursts out of body,"},{"time":452207,"text":"yadda yadda yadda, you know the drill."},{"time":454396,"text":"(Laughter) (Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":457626,"text":"Now I would argue that, once stung,"},{"time":460506,"text":"the cockroach isn't a roach anymore."},{"time":462511,"text":"It's more of an extension of the wasp,"},{"time":464861,"text":"just like the cricket was an\nextension of the Gordian worm."},{"time":467719,"text":"These hosts won't get to survive or reproduce."},{"time":470519,"text":"They have as much control over their own fates"},{"time":472318,"text":"as my car."},{"time":474102,"text":"Once the parasites get in,"},{"time":475602,"text":"the hosts don't get a say."}]},{"cues":[{"time":478167,"text":"Now humans, of course,"},{"time":479481,"text":"are no stranger to manipulation."},{"time":481513,"text":"We take drugs to shift the chemistries of our brains"},{"time":483873,"text":"and to change our moods,"},{"time":485004,"text":"and what are arguments or advertising or big ideas"},{"time":489024,"text":"if not an attempt to influence someone else's mind?"},{"time":492727,"text":"But our attempts at doing this"},{"time":494254,"text":"are crude and blundering compared"},{"time":496032,"text":"to the fine-grained specificity of the parasites."},{"time":499127,"text":"Don Draper only wishes he was as elegant"},{"time":501519,"text":"and precise as the emerald cockroach wasp."},{"time":506479,"text":"Now, I think this is part of what makes parasites"},{"time":510219,"text":"so sinister and so compelling."},{"time":513005,"text":"We place such a premium on our free will"},{"time":515627,"text":"and our independence"},{"time":516888,"text":"that the prospect of losing those qualities"},{"time":518469,"text":"to forces unseen"},{"time":519747,"text":"informs many of our deepest societal fears."},{"time":522915,"text":"Orwellian dystopias and shadowy cabals"},{"time":525368,"text":"and mind-controlling supervillains --"},{"time":527222,"text":"these are tropes that fill our darkest fiction,"},{"time":530250,"text":"but in nature, they happen all the time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":535048,"text":"Which leads me to an obvious"},{"time":537680,"text":"and disquieting question:"},{"time":539980,"text":"Are there dark, sinister parasites"},{"time":541703,"text":"that are influencing our behavior"},{"time":543659,"text":"without us knowing about it,"},{"time":545234,"text":"besides the NSA?"},{"time":548053,"text":"If there are any —"},{"time":549360,"text":"(Laughter) (Applause)"},{"time":553326,"text":"I've got a red dot on my forehead now, don't I?"},{"time":555648,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":558175,"text":"If there are any, this is a good candidate for them."},{"time":561129,"text":"This is Toxoplasma gondii, or Toxo, for short,"},{"time":564407,"text":"because the terrifying creature"},{"time":565996,"text":"always deserves a cute nickname."},{"time":568206,"text":"Toxo infects mammals,"},{"time":570488,"text":"a wide variety of mammals,"},{"time":571966,"text":"but it can only sexually reproduce in a cat."},{"time":575047,"text":"And scientists like Joanne Webster have shown that"},{"time":577808,"text":"if Toxo gets into a rat or a mouse,"},{"time":580001,"text":"it turns the rodent into a cat-seeking missile."},{"time":583473,"text":"If the infected rat smells the delightful odor"},{"time":586549,"text":"of cat piss,"},{"time":587773,"text":"it runs towards the source of the smell"},{"time":590493,"text":"rather than the more sensible direction of away."},{"time":594412,"text":"The cat eats the rat. Toxo gets to have sex."},{"time":596947,"text":"It's a classic tale of Eat, Prey, Love."},{"time":599819,"text":"(Laughter) (Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":607512,"text":"You're very charitable, generous people."},{"time":610714,"text":"Hi, Elizabeth, I loved your talk."}]},{"cues":[{"time":613299,"text":"How does the parasite control its host"},{"time":616667,"text":"in this way?"},{"time":617871,"text":"We don't really know."},{"time":619197,"text":"We know that Toxo releases an enzyme"},{"time":620885,"text":"that makes dopamine, a substance involved"},{"time":622877,"text":"in reward and motivation."},{"time":624690,"text":"We know it targets certain parts of a rodent's brain,"},{"time":627121,"text":"including those involved in sexual arousal."},{"time":629586,"text":"But how those puzzle pieces fit together"},{"time":631787,"text":"is not immediately clear."},{"time":633631,"text":"What is clear is that this thing"},{"time":635927,"text":"is a single cell."},{"time":637319,"text":"This has no nervous system."},{"time":638689,"text":"It has no consciousness."},{"time":639821,"text":"It doesn't even have a body."},{"time":641122,"text":"But it's manipulating a mammal?"},{"time":643746,"text":"We are mammals."},{"time":645172,"text":"We are more intelligent than a mere rat, to be sure,"},{"time":647606,"text":"but our brains have the same basic structure,"},{"time":650130,"text":"the same types of cells,"},{"time":651523,"text":"the same chemicals running through them,"},{"time":653111,"text":"and the same parasites."},{"time":655430,"text":"Estimates vary a lot, but some figures suggest"},{"time":657778,"text":"that one in three people around the world"},{"time":660138,"text":"have Toxo in their brains."},{"time":661851,"text":"Now typically, this doesn't lead to any overt illness."},{"time":665339,"text":"The parasite holds up in a dormant state"},{"time":667217,"text":"for a long period of time."},{"time":669400,"text":"But there's some evidence that those people"},{"time":671439,"text":"who are carriers score slightly differently"},{"time":674473,"text":"on personality questionnaires than other people,"},{"time":677202,"text":"that they have a slightly \nhigher risk of car accidents,"},{"time":679686,"text":"and there's some evidence\nthat people with schizophrenia"},{"time":682289,"text":"are more likely to be infected."},{"time":684835,"text":"Now, I think this evidence is still inconclusive,"},{"time":687018,"text":"and even among Toxo researchers,"},{"time":688929,"text":"opinion is divided as to whether the parasite"},{"time":691369,"text":"is truly influencing our behavior."},{"time":693754,"text":"But given the widespread\nnature of such manipulations,"},{"time":696413,"text":"it would be completely implausible"},{"time":698258,"text":"for humans to be the only species"},{"time":699907,"text":"that weren't similarly affected."}]},{"cues":[{"time":702853,"text":"And I think that this capacity to constantly"},{"time":707246,"text":"subvert our way of thinking about the world"},{"time":710113,"text":"makes parasites amazing."},{"time":711660,"text":"They're constantly inviting us to\nlook at the natural world sideways,"},{"time":714869,"text":"and to ask if the behaviors we're seeing,"},{"time":717040,"text":"whether they're simple and obvious"},{"time":718527,"text":"or baffling and puzzling,"},{"time":720060,"text":"are not the results of individuals"},{"time":722146,"text":"acting through their own accord"},{"time":723999,"text":"but because they are being bent"},{"time":725808,"text":"to the control of something else."},{"time":728478,"text":"And while that idea may be disquieting,"},{"time":730518,"text":"and while parasites' habits may be very grisly,"},{"time":733441,"text":"I think that ability to surprise us"},{"time":735233,"text":"makes them as wonderful and as charismatic"},{"time":738408,"text":"as any panda or butterfly or dolphin."}]},{"cues":[{"time":741772,"text":"At the end of \"On the Origin of Species,\""},{"time":743991,"text":"Charles Darwin writes about the grandeur of life,"},{"time":746980,"text":"and of endless forms most beautiful"},{"time":749633,"text":"and most wonderful,"},{"time":751065,"text":"and I like to think he could easily have been talking"},{"time":753644,"text":"about a tapeworm that makes shrimp sociable"},{"time":756824,"text":"or a wasp that takes cockroaches for walks."}]},{"cues":[{"time":760073,"text":"But perhaps, that's just a parasite talking."}]},{"cues":[{"time":763222,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":764953,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}